{
  "texts": [
    "Through object detection technology, intelligent vehicles can perceive the positions of vehicles and determine drivable areas in the current environment.",
    "Simultaneously, this information is provided to the back-end decision-making system, enhancing the safety of intelligent vehicles [2].",
    "In summary, conducting appropriate detection in traffic scenarios helps reduce the risks associated with autonomous driving systems.Traditional object detection algorithms usually include three main steps.",
    "The first step is to mark potential regions in the input image that may contain objects.",
    "The second step is to extract features from these marked candidate regions, which can include methods like Histogram of Oriented Gradients (HOG) [3], Scale-Invariant Feature Transform (SIFT) [4], Viola-Jones Haar-like features (Haar) [5] and others."
  ]
}